&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s the difference between &lt;code&gt;addEventListener&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;onclick&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; h = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable language_&quot;&gt;document&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;getElementById&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;a&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
h.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;onclick&lt;/span&gt; = dothing1;
h.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;addEventListener&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;click&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, dothing2);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code above resides together in a separate .js file, and they both work perfectly.&lt;/p&gt;
